@@ -0,0 +1,81 @@
+# p2pandaapp-cli-gomod
+
+This example implements a chat CLI using puregotk with the standard Go build system.
+
+First, make sure the `libp2panda` library is built and installed on your system (see [../p2panda-gobject-go/](../p2panda-gobject-go) for instructions).
+
+To then run the chat using the standard Go build system:
+
+```shell
+go generate ./...
+
+go run ./cmd/p2pandaapp-cli-gomod-chat/
+```
+
+To run the bootstrap node:
+
+```shell
+go run ./cmd/p2pandaapp-cli-gomod-bootstrap/
+```
+
+Connect two chat peers on the same local network (mDNS):
+
+```shell
+# Terminal 1
+go run ./cmd/p2pandaapp-cli-gomod-chat/
+
+# Terminal 2
+go run ./cmd/p2pandaapp-cli-gomod-chat/
+```
+
+Connect two chat peers across networks using a bootstrap:
+
+```shell
+# Terminal 1 (or a server): start a bootstrap node
+go run ./cmd/p2pandaapp-cli-gomod-bootstrap/
+# Prints: <node-id-hex>
+
+# Terminal 2: connect via the bootstrap
+go run ./cmd/p2pandaapp-cli-gomod-chat/ --peer <node-id-hex>
+
+# Terminal 3: connect via the bootstrap or directly via another peer
+go run ./cmd/p2pandaapp-cli-gomod-chat/ --peer <node-id-hex>
+```
+
+Alternatively, you can build and run the chat using Flatpak, which will also build `libp2panda` for you:
+
+```shell
+flatpak-builder --force-clean --disable-rofiles-fuse --user --repo=repo --install builddir page.codeberg.puregotk.P2PandaAppCLIGomod.json
+
+flatpak run page.codeberg.puregotk.P2PandaAppCLIGomod
+```
+
+To run the bootstrap node using Flatpak:
+
+```shell
+flatpak run --command=p2pandaapp-cli-gomod-bootstrap page.codeberg.puregotk.P2PandaAppCLIGomod
+```
+
+Connect two chat peers on the same local network (mDNS) using Flatpak:
+
+```shell
+# Terminal 1
+flatpak run page.codeberg.puregotk.P2PandaAppCLIGomod
+
+# Terminal 2
+flatpak run page.codeberg.puregotk.P2PandaAppCLIGomod
+```
+
+Connect two chat peers across networks using a bootstrap using Flatpak:
+
+```shell
+# Terminal 1 (or a server): start a bootstrap node
+flatpak run --command=p2pandaapp-cli-gomod-bootstrap page.codeberg.puregotk.P2PandaAppCLIGomod
+# Prints: <node-id-hex>
+
+# Terminal 2: connect via the bootstrap
+flatpak run page.codeberg.puregotk.P2PandaAppCLIGomod --peer <node-id-hex>
+
+# Terminal 3: connect via the bootstrap or directly via another peer
+flatpak run page.codeberg.puregotk.P2PandaAppCLIGomod --peer <node-id-hex>
+```
